File: Motorists navigate their way as power supply is switched off during load-shedding. AFP/Rodger Bosch JOHANNESBURG - Eskom is suspending load-shedding on Friday afternoon. But before you get excited, it's not for your benefit. READ: Load-shedding to continue until Friday It's only to ensure a virtual sitting of Parliament. The load-shedding suspension will take place from midday to 5pm Friday evening to help Parliament pass a number of Appropriation Bills. READ: Stage 2 load-shedding to be implemented from 4pm According to the power utility, passing the bills is essential for government operations. They affect a number of state functions like hospitals and law enforcement. Load-shedding will resume from 5pm. #PowerAlert1
